[SN]TITLE[SN]
Fire engine battling A50 fire catches fire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A fire engine called out to a car fire was set alight itself when a lorry crashed into it.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Firefighters were putting out the blaze on the A50 near Aston-on-Trent, Derbyshire, when the lorry hit their fire engine, causing both to ignite.
The fires broke out on the eastbound carriageway but both carriageways have been closed, causing stationary traffic and long delays.
Motorists have been advised to avoid the area.
